init_text: Following World War III, all the nations of the world agreed to 50 years of strict isolation from one another in order to prevent additional conflicts. 50 years later, the United States comes out of exile, only to learn that no one else went into isolation.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They would be filled with the most bizarre stories about how life in America had been.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The United States was in shambles.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Due to this lack of legislation and the subsequent lapse in security, all government records were gone.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: In the end, the United States was destroyed by a new type of bomb.
